ctf budddy is a simple discord bot that helps users find and organiz teams for CTF's. The bot allows a user to react to a message and randomly assigns them into a team.

Commands

!ctf_lfg <CTF_NAME>
Starts a new lfg request

The bot will send a message:
React with âœ… if you are looking for a team for HackTheBox!
Users then react to the message to participate.

!ctf_team TS=<TEAM_SIZE>
Creates random teams with the specified team size from users who reacted.

Example:
!ctf_team TS=4

The bot will then respond with:

**CTF Teams for HackTheBox:**

**Team 1:** @user1 @user2 @user3 @user4

**Team 2:** @user5 @user6 @user7 @user8


!ctf_help
Displays a help message explaining commands.

Setup Instructions

Prerequisites:

Python 3.9+

Docker (optional, for containerized deployment)

A Discord bot token

Python Set up:

Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/your-repo/CTF_Buddy.git
cd CTF_Buddy

Install dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt

Create a .env file and add your bot token:
DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN= instert_bot_token_here

Run the bot:
python ctf_Buddy.py

Docker Deployment:

Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/your-repo/CTF_Buddyy.git
cd CTF_Buddy

Build the Docker image:
docker build -t ctf-buddy .

Run the container :
docker run --name ctf-buddy ctf-buddy
